1) Update the button text

Open:

snippets/buy-buttons.liquid

Find this block:

{%- else -%}
  {{ 'products.product.add_to_cart' | t }}
{%- endif -%}

Replace it with:

{%- else -%}
  Buy Now
{%- endif -%}

If you want, you can keep the original translation and only show Buy Now on this product later, but this is the fastest version.

2) Redirect to checkout instead of cart

Open:

assets/product-form.js

Find this section:

} else if (!this.cart) {
  window.location = window.routes.cart_url;
  return;
}

Replace it with:

async handleSubmit(evt) {
  evt.preventDefault();

  if (this.submitButton.getAttribute('aria-disabled') === 'true') return;

  this.handleErrorMessage();

  this.submitButton.setAttribute('aria-disabled', true);
  this.submitButton.classList.add('loading');
  this.querySelector('.loading__spinner').classList.remove('hidden');

  const formData = new FormData(this.form);

  try {
    await fetch('/cart/clear.js', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        Accept: 'application/json'
      }
    });

    const addResponse = await fetch('/cart/add.js', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: {
        Accept: 'application/json'
      },
      body: formData
    });

    const addResult = await addResponse.json();

    if (addResult.status) {
      this.handleErrorMessage(addResult.description || 'Something went wrong.');
      return;
    }

    window.location.href = '/checkout';
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error);
    this.handleErrorMessage('Something went wrong. Please try again.');
  } finally {
    this.submitButton.classList.remove('loading');
    this.querySelector('.loading__spinner').classList.add('hidden');
    this.submitButton.removeAttribute('aria-disabled');
  }
}

That is the key change.

3) Optional: turn off cart drawer behavior too

Right now, if a cart drawer exists, the theme will still render the drawer instead of redirecting.

In the same file, find this block near the bottom of the success path:

const quickAddModal = this.closest('quick-add-modal');
if (quickAddModal) {
  document.body.addEventListener(
    'modalClosed',
    () => {
      setTimeout(() => {
        CartPerformance.measure("add:paint-updated-sections", () => {
          this.cart.renderContents(response);
        });
      });
    },
    { once: true }
  );
  quickAddModal.hide(true);
} else {
  CartPerformance.measure("add:paint-updated-sections", () => {
    this.cart.renderContents(response);
  });
}

Replace that whole block with:

window.location = '/checkout';
return;

That makes the behavior consistent:

selected bundle variant gets added
selected quantity gets added
customer goes straight to checkout

This is the version I’d use for your store.

Best final version for your file

Inside assets/product-form.js, after this line:

} else if (!this.cart) {
  window.location = '/checkout';
  return;
}

replace the drawer-render section with:

window.location = '/checkout';
return;

So the success path always goes to checkout.

Important test after editing

Do these 4 checks:

Select 2x Pick Maker (Most Popular)
Change quantity to 2
Click Buy Now
Confirm checkout shows:
correct bundle variant
correct quantity
no cart step in between

If quantity or variant fails, then we tighten it further, but Dawn usually handles this correctly because the form already submits the active variant and quantity.

One caution

If you still have the dynamic checkout button enabled anywhere, turn it off in the theme editor so it does not conflict with your custom Buy Now flow.
